> My warrior 48 with buffs of 49 cleric = 3205 hp<br>
<br>
Celstial Heal: 450 mana for 1496 hp of healing.<br>
Cheal: 400 mana for 3000 hp of healing<br>
<br>
Celstial Heal: 900 mana for 2996 hp of healing.<br>
Cheal: 400 mana for 3000 hp of healing<br>
<br>
Cheal + Skill = Efficiency<br>
Cheal + 90% of Norrath = Inefficiency<br>
<br>
Really I think this is THE test of a cleric.  Ever notice how one night you'll get a cleric that just seems to always have mana?  Hrmm.... next night OOM OOM OOM is all you hear.  Why do I say it's the test?  Because a cleric who can hit cheal correctly, regardless of situation, means they are an efficient cleric.  Mana efficiency and it's juggling is the divining line.<br>
<br>
I know a cleric who when I first started grouping with them, I was constantly sweating.  After several times with them, I began to trust them.  Because even though I only had 1/2 a bubble left, they always, always, always got the cheal off in time.  Regardless of whether there was 1 mob, 2 mobs, 3 mobs or more.<br>
<br>
Anyway, this is my opinion.  I'm not a cleric, but I do know that every time I've died recently it is because the cleric was trying to use celestial heal while a mob was doing 500 hp of damage per second, and the greatest clerics I've ever known are ones who used cheal efficiently.<br>
<br>
Me <p><br>
Minute Manaslayer<br>
60th Sage Charmer<br>
Realm Brell Serilis<br>
<a href="mailto:Minute@vastempire.net">My E-Mail</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uqualous.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qualous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/18/01 1:54:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question to the clerics</span><hr size=1> One thing to realize with debuffing mobs like Naggy and Vox is that Celestial Heal is a short term buff.  For those mobs I generally will stick to the burst-type of heals because you could just spending your mana on a heal that is going to be debuffed during the next AoE. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujagr11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jagr11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/18/01 4:09:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question to the clerics</span><hr size=1> in raid type situations like with naggy and vox, plane raids, etc.. celestial healing isn't much help(except for touching up at the end, as some people have said earlier). <br>
<br>
those type of mobs have ae and melee dmg that is too fast for celestial healing to keep up. Divine light, remedy, and cheal are all i have ever used on raids.<br>
<br>
I only use celestial healing when I am doing exp groups and such where the dmg to the tanks is not much, and it does a nice job keeping up with it and saves the cleric alot of mana then. On raids you wont see that, hehe. clerics will always be screaming for a necro to dump man to them.<br>
<br>
Just some stuff I have picked up in my experiences from being a healer. Hope it helps.<br>
<br>
Jagr Jones<br>
56 Templar<br>
Ethereal Knighthood<br>
