 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/18/01 5:19:48 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question to the clerics</span><hr size=1> Something else to think about is this:<br>
<br>
On my more recent raids, after self buffs, druid buffs and shammie buffs I have a full buff bar. I have so many buffs at my disposile that I have to forgo some because it will take me over 15. Add a Bard to the mix and I have even a harder time with it.<br>
<br>
I do alot of Stunning in battle and DT healing. I also try to watch Shammies and Necros for needing heals as they are trying to regain mana. C2 is needed. Doggie Form helps the Att stats, WW form is better. Dex helps with getting one of my weapons to proc. HP/AC/Resist buffs are a must (min 5 slots). STA buffs increase both HP and, in my mind anyway, my effectiveness in long battles. Haste is a must. AGI helps defense and weapon skill gain. STR is almost always given. Regen is a must have. Add a Circle and Tuna, we are now up to 14 buffs. Then add to that the fact that as a Dwarf who can't jump worth squat and is constantly being stuck behind walls of tall humans and even worse Barbarians, Ogres and Trolls, DMF is almost a must have. <br>
<br>
There you have it, a full buff bar. Where is your Celestrial Heal going to go? <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglesig.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showMessage?topicID=6945.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showMessage?topicID=6938.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.threadControl?topicID=6935.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6935.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=6935.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="brellserilisfrm48">Town Crier (Rules & Announcements)<option value="brellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion">The Commons (General EQ Discussion)<option value="brellserilisfrm56">Salutations & Congratulations <option value="brellserilisfrm33">Dreams & Diversions (Off Topic)<option value="brellserilisfrm55">Fellowship of Guilds (Guildchat)<option value="brellserilisbrellslairadminonly">Brell's Lair (Admin only)<option value="brellserilismeleetalk">Tome: Races